# Bot (`apps/bot`)

## Env

`TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `API_BASE_URL` (server origin), `BOT_INTERNAL_TOKEN` (must match server).

## Architecture

- **Entry:** `src/index.ts` — registers command modules, `bot.catch` logging.
- **API:** `services/apiClient.ts` — `verifyNafdac`, `recordBotActivity`, `initializeBotProCheckout`, `fetchBotStatus`; headers `x-internal-bot-token`, Telegram user fields (URI-encoded for header safety).
- **Commands:** `commands/verifyCommand.ts` (`/verify`, inline flow, `/upgrade`), `commands/statusCommand.ts` (`/status`).
- **UX:** `verifyButtonMarkup` for consistent keyboards; HTML replies where escaped content is controlled.

## Server endpoints used

- `POST /api/bot/activity`
- `POST /api/bot/status` — `{ telegramId }`
- `POST /api/bot/billing/initialize-bot-pro` — `{ telegramId }`
- `GET /api/verify/:nafdac` with bot headers

## Conventions

- ESM with **`.js` imports** in source; keep messages clear for **free vs Bot Pro** (avoid implying Pro users are on “free tier”).
